{
  "stem": "7781.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were-- they were always dangerous, but only getting worse.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In 1936, they had the pogrom in Lodz, not a big one, but they used to, you know, to go into Jewish homes and-- and destroy everything.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you could feel it, that the press, the-- the-- you know, the government turned more anti-semitic.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, you could feel it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 97,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We didn't talk about leaving.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 97,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We just talked about the situation, that there was-- we had no means to leave.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 97,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we lived for so many hundreds of years.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 97,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was a youngster, I-- especially me, I didn't think about leaving.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 97,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If they talked about it I don't know, but we didn't have the means of-- of leaving.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 98,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were always afraid, always talking about it's getting bad, and it's getting worse every-- every day.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 98,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we were trapped.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 98,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 98,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He didn't have a place where to go.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 99,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there was really no way to consider leaving.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Was no place to leaving.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't have the means, and we have no-- we didn't have a place where to.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that was home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 101,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What time is it?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Are you going to continue for another half hour, then we have lunch?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 103,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now--",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
